                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="51976" author="adilger" created="Thu, 7 Feb 2013 10:50:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Closing this as a duplicate of &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-2754&quot; title=&quot;rename from MDT1 to MDT0 sometimes appears to succeed but does not&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-2754&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-2754&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, since the symptoms are similar, and they will be fixed by the same patch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="51944" author="di.wang" created="Thu, 7 Feb 2013 01:06:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This can be fixed by &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/#change,5257&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/#change,5257&lt;/a&gt; as well.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="51900" author="adilger" created="Wed, 6 Feb 2013 14:01:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;John, it would also be good to create new test cases if there is testing that you are doing by hand that is not being caught by existing regression tests.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="51898" author="adilger" created="Wed, 6 Feb 2013 13:59:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Deleting a remote directory should work fine with &quot;rm -r&quot; or &quot;rmdir&quot;, and should not need any special handling in userspace.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think this is related to &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-2755&quot; title=&quot;calling rmdir on remote directory returns -ENOENT instead of -EBUSY&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-2755&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-2755&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, and there should NOT be special handling of deleting remote entries.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
